  schema:description "Queen’s Diamond Jubilee medal recipient Chris is one of Canada’s hottest musicians for kids. He has been hailed as a “Children’s musical star” (National Post) and “Canada’s greatest eco-troubadour for young people” (Mississauga Living Arts). Everything Chris does comes from the heart, and he has been delighting audiences with his joyful songs and exotic world instruments for three decades, reaching over 1 million children live in concert, with hit performances on YTV’s Treehouse, TVO’, Mr. Dressup,  and the CBC.";
