iwts_performer:2265 a schema:Person;
  schema:name "Neelima Raju";
  schema:description "I am a Kuchipudi (Traditional Indian Dance/Theatre) Dancer and Choreographer. I have learnt the technique of dance/theatre, and music in a mentorship model in India. Having performed as a soloist for twenty years I have won the approval of critics, and general audiences. I am also the recipient of the NJ State Heritage Fellowship (FY 2026) administered by the NJ State Arts Council. My choreography is based on the traditional idiom yet explores new dimensions of Kuchipudi.";
