iwts_performer:3699 a schema:Person;
  schema:name "Jen Kober";
  schema:description "Jen Kober lives in Baton Rouge and brings her souther sass to the comedy stage. Dry Bar Comedy lovers adore her hard-hitting hour as she commands the stage and dares you not to laugh. She is the winner of NPR's Snap Judgement Comedic Performance of the Year for her Girl Scout Cookie story which went viral upon its release.  She can be seen on Disney+ in The Mandalorian and Diary of a Future President, on HBO’S Hacks, Showtime’s Black Monday and American Horror Story and Netflix: Dead to Me, and in June '26 streaming on Comedy Dynamics.";
