  schema:description "Since dropping out of college in 2007, Jacob Johnson has crossed the country in six (so far)minivans, delivering his high-energy, “highly caffeinated” acoustic guitar style to audiences nationwide. He has shared stages with Grammy winners Tommy Emmanuel and Victor Wooten, plus Phil Keaggy, Marcus King, and Tim Reynolds. A Don Gibson Songwriter Award Grand Prize winner, he has performed at Falcon Ridge, Walnut Valley, Wildflower, and festivals across the U.S.";
