iwts_performer:5142 a schema:Person;
  schema:name "Pat Hazell's The Wonder Bread Years";
  schema:description "Showtime declared Pat Hazell one of the five funniest people in America. Hazell is one of the original writers for NBC's Seinfeld, a veteran of The Tonight Show and a critically-acclaimed playwright. Pat hosts the Arts & Culture podcast Creativity in Captivity. He is the creator of the The Wonder Bread Years, a fresh and funny salute to Americana.   He has been hailed by Jerry Seinfeld as 'Milk-snorting funny!' Hazell's other shows include \"Pat Hazell’s Permanent Record\", \"The Good Humor Men\" and \"My Funny Valentine\"";
