iwts_performer:6735 a schema:Person;
  schema:name "Leslie McCurdy";
  schema:description "Award winning, internationally recognized, solo performing artist, Leslie McCurdy, has many stage, film and TV credits but is most \"famous\" for the one-woman plays that she wrote and performs. Those include, \"The Spirit of Harriet Tubman\", \"Things My Fore-Sisters Saw,\" and \"Lady Ain't Singin' No Blues\". She has also created a two person musical entitled, \"The Darktown Strutters Ball\".  She has received critical acclaim, rave reviews and is lauded for her \"brilliance\" and the messages of social consciousness that are instilled through her work.";
