iwts_performer:7655 a schema:PerformingGroup;
  schema:name "Marla Feeney";
  schema:description "Multi-instrumentalist (violin, saxes, clarinets, flute, bagpipes)  and vocalist, Marla Feeney is one of Atlanta's favorite performers. She is featured in her Klezmer band , her World music band, and her leading role in Bonaventure Quartet (Atlanta's Best known Gypsy jazz band), The Border Collies (lead fiddle in Irish Band),as well as special guest in a number of jazz bands. Before coming to Atlanta, several years ago, Marla ran shows in Branson. Marla holds 2 masters (clarinet and violin), and keeps busy teaching multiple instruments.";
