iwts_performer:8343 a schema:PerformingGroup;
  schema:name "Nathan";
  schema:description """I HAVE NO IDEA is a hilarious, heartfelt, and poignant new play, with original music, exploring adult ADHD.

The play follows besties Robin and Taylor as they support each other through their ADHD journeys, including their interactions with mental health professionals. Using humour, empathy, music, and the lived experiences of the playwright and creative team, it deals with the barriers neurodivergent people face, provides a voice for neurodivergent people of all ages, and gives neurotypical people insight into the lives of ADHDers.""";
