  schema:description "Ample Man Danse has been creating and producing indoor and in situ choreographic works since 2012. In an approach that values citizen involvement, Simon Ampleman and his collaborators explore the “human effect” by multiplying creative exchanges with communities, in Quebec and internationally. Interactive and accessible, our artistic objects honor the talent of their creators and act as vectors of cultural and social development.";
