iwts_performer:9355 a schema:Person;
  schema:name "Mark Crissinger";
  schema:description """After twenty fantastic years in the Southern Ontario music scene Mark Crissinger moved to British Columbia in 2007. Since 2009 he has been building a solo career, playing over 100 shows a year on Vancouver Island, the BC lower mainland, ON & QC. He has released six studio albums, four live albums, and been nominated for a Maple Blues Award. 
Blending traditional themes, clever lyrics, and modern arrangements, Mark performs original folk-rock & blues music that reveals his singer-songwriter soul and the blues in his heart.""";
