iwts_performer:9384 a schema:Person;
  schema:name "Margo";
  schema:description """Cree-Saulteaux performing artist, Margo Kane is the Founder and Artistic Managing Director of Full Circle: First Nations Performance. For over 50 years she has been active as an actor, performing artist and community cultural worker. 

Her desire to share artistic performance that has meaning for her people is the catalyst for her extensive work, travels and consultation within Indigenous communities across Canada and abroad.

She developed and runs the annual Talking Stick Festival which celebrating its 20th Anniversary in 2021.""";
