iwts_performer:9427 a schema:Person;
  schema:name "Vanessa Marcoux";
  schema:description "Vanessa Marcoux is a violinist and composer based in Montreal. Throughout her career, she has received numerous grants and awards, and most recently, an Opus prize for her latest album \"Cendres\".  She has played worldwide, and her musical activities range from classical and contemporary music to world music, jazz and improvisation.  She is also a founding member of Duo Cordelia, a Montreal-based ensemble that is very active on the Canadian music scene.  She has released two albums, \"La jungle\" (2023) and \"Cendres\", both acclaimed critically.";
