  schema:description "Tight-as-can-be three-part harmonic explosions wrapped in a gritty, primal, snarling exterior, Bad Buddy (Edmonton, Alberta) is quoted as being “a force to be reckoned with” (SONiC 102.9). The electric energy of their live show is only amplified by the exceptional songwriting ability possessed by the band. The female-fronted Motown-surf-punk band commands attention, painting strong, feminist, sonic pictures drawn from real-life inspirations. Picture The Shirelles meets The Ramones meets Queen.";
