iwts_performer:9495 a schema:Person;
  schema:name "Deantha Edmunds";
  schema:description """Deantha Edmunds, Canada’s first Inuk professional classical singer, was appointed to the Order of Canada in 2023. In 2024, she received Newfoundland & Labrador’s Premier’s Medal for the Arts and was named Arts NL’s “Artist of the Year.”

Nominated for a 2025 JUNO for Angmalukisaa (Classical Composition of the Year) and Alikeness (Classical Album of the Year), she is also up for “Indigenous Artist of the Year” at the 2025 East Coast Music Awards.""";
