iwts_performer:10273 a schema:Person;
  schema:name "Genean Hines Grobe (Genean L'Artiste)";
  schema:description """Genean Hines Grobe (Genean L'Artiste) is an interdisciplinary artist working at the intersection of movement, storytelling, and emotional truth. Her work explores what lives in the body—grief, joy, rupture, healing—and gives it form through performance. Rooted in lived experience, Genean creates spaces where the unspoken can be seen, felt, and released. A trauma survivor, Genean offers audiences raw, authentic artistry to catalyze emotional awareness, inquiry, and healing. 
Training: Actors Studio Drama School (New York City), The Ailey School""";
