  schema:description "Cirque Alfonse is a contemporary circus collective founded in 2005 by siblings Antoine Carabinier-Lépine and Julie Lépine. Its members have worked with leading “nouveau cirque” companies worldwide. The troupe includes professional acrobats trained at the École nationale de cirque de Montréal, a dancer, a former skiing champion, and three versatile musicians. Based on the family farm in Saint-Alphonse-Rodriguez, the troupe creates original, award-winning shows in a converted barn, blending tradition, innovation, and a strong sense of community.";
