iwts_performer:10365 a schema:PerformingGroup;
  schema:name "The Bery Groovy Things Band";
  schema:description """Consisting of four of Winnipeg’s finest singers and and an all star band, the Very Groovy Things specializes in music from the mid 60s to the early 70s. The core of the group’s repertoire comes from the Mamas and the Papas, but their set list also includes music from the '60s Laurel Canyon Scene, as well as some tunes from the British Invasion.Some of the hits include California Dreamin’, Monday Monday and 1230.
Brit hits include To Sir With Love and Don’t Letbtye Sun Catch You Crying. Jodie Borle leads the powerful group of vocalists .""";
